    "en": "Selfridge's conjectures",
    "ja": null,
    "latex": "A number `p` satisfies the *Selfridge condition* if\n1. `p` is odd,\n2. `p ≡ ± 2 (mod 5)`,\n3. `2^(p-1) ≡ 1 (mod p)`\n4. `(p+1).fib ≡ 0 (mod p)`\n\n\nThis is the condition that is tested in the PSW conjecture.\nNote: this is non-standard terminology. -/\n@[mk_iff]\nstructure IsSelfridge (p : ℕ) where\n  is_odd : Odd p\n  mod_5 : p ≡ 2 [MOD 5] ∨ p ≡ 3 [MOD 5]\n  pow_2 : 2^(p-1) ≡ 1 [MOD p]\n  fib : (p+1).fib ≡ 0",
    "preview_source": "formal-conjectures"
  },
